headline: Why HP (HPQ) Stock Is Trading Up Today
summary: Shares of personal computing and printing company HP (NYSE:HPQ) jumped 5.9% in the afternoon session after the company announced it had commenced operations at a new manufacturing facility and an AI Research & Development Center in Saudi Arabia. The new factory, located in Riyadh, began by producing the HP EliteDesk AI PC and was set to expand its production line.
